text: Gardner Farmstead, on Licking Station Rd. near Salyersville, Kentucky was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2015. With 17 photos from 2014-15. The main house was built c.1830 as a two-story dog-trot log house built of half-dovetail notched logs, and evolved to be a five-bay I-house with a rear ell. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Kentucky Category:Magoffin County, Kentucky Category:1830 establishments in Kentucky
title: Gardner Farmstead
